title: For Sale/Trade:  Smith and Wesson 5906 Tactical 9mm
postcontent: The best all Stainleess steel Smith ever, made to Performance Center specs. Developed for Law Enforcement and Military use the 5906 Tactical was made to be as tough as they could make it with the slide and frame machined from a single block of stainless steel and remaining as a matched pair throughout assembly. The slide rests on larger full length rails and rides nearly inside the frame much as a CZ design ( and this gun was made in the late 80's). Smith also developed a delayed-unlock firing system for these that lessened felt recoil for quicker target acqusition and equipped them with three dot Novak sights (this one has trijicon night sights but they are very weak), loaded chamber window and decocker/safety . Most came with an accessory rail but some did not but mounting points are still on the bottom of the slide. This was a duty weapon at one time and shows some wear from being carried but bore is still bright and internal wear is minimal, plenty of years left in this gun. These are getting harder to find as people realize what fine and collectible weapons they are so the asking price is 550 or a trade of 600 value. Comes with two 15 round magazines and a hard plastc case.
